# B2: Operator constraint violated — warning expected.
# `lesser` is annotated with `<(a, a) => a -> a -> a`, meaning it needs `<`
# to work for the argument type.  Passing blocks (which `<` does not accept)
# violates the constraint, so a type warning should be emitted.
` { type: "<(a, a) => a -> a -> a" }
lesser(x, y): if(x < y, x, y)
result: lesser({n: 1}, {n: 2})
` { type: "number" }
check: result
